{
  "stem": "7282.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I, I do have-- I'll, I'll show you later on the picture of the-- of the minyan, the rabbi, his name is right in the picture, in the book.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I'll show you it later.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So, well, I mean, on Saturdays and in the holidays, we used to go there.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because my father was a Chusid of the rabbi.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And when he passed away, the gabbai took it over.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the old Hasidim would belong to the congregation before used to go to the-- to the gabbai on Saturdays, only Saturdays and the holidays.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That's what I remember.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "What language did you speak at home?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, at home, we spoke Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was the only language.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it was, actually is-- belonged to Poland.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But it was a lot Ukrainian--",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--word.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I had lots of friends in the beginning.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I'll start on Ha-no'ar Ha-Ziyyoni.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When I was about 10, 11, or 12 years, I belonged to an organization, Ha-no'ar Ha-Ziyyoni.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And there, we had, I mean, like, it was a [NON-ENGLISH], or it was several [NON-ENGLISH], I mean, according to the age or what.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the most I, I been there, it was one the name Katz, too, but not a relative.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "His name was-- the first name was Friedl-- we used to call him [NON-ENGLISH]-- Katz.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Then it was Zalman Szejdenberg what is still-- I mean, he was a captain in Russia.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "During the war, he was in jail because he was-- he was [NON-ENGLISH] in, in the-- in the Hashomer-- Ha-no'ar Ha-Ziyyoni.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then it was [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Muni Smik.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I met him in, in Russia after the war.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then it was Joski Mela.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He is still in, in Israel.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
